  "texts": [
    "Reddit TL;DR Summarization (Völske et al., 2017): This dataset 2 includes forum posts from Reddit, specifically collected for summarization purposes, along with corresponding preference labels.",
    "In line with prior research (Stiennon et al., 2020), we employ a refined version of this dataset to train our SFT policy, leveraging its preference labels during the alignment process.",
    "UltraFeedback Binarized (Cui et al., 2023; Tunstall et al., 2023): This dataset foot_3 comprises 64,000 prompts, each associated with four different completions produced by a mix of open-source and proprietary models.",
    "GPT-4 evaluates these completions, assigning scores based on factors such as helpfulness and honesty.",
    "Binary preference pairs are created by selecting the completion with the highest average score as the \"accepted\" response, while one of the other three is chosen randomly to serve as the \"rejected\" response."
  ],
